<p>These are generic enough to apply to smart-contract languages as-is. The=
 prompt explicitly asks for <strong>syntactically valid mutations only</str=
ong> =E2=80=94 anything that fails to parse is rejected later in the <a hre=
f=3D"https://nowarp.io/blog/compiler-testing-part-1#validating-mutators">Va=
lidating phase</a>.</p>
<p>The LLM occasionally hallucinates impossible combinations (e.g. <code>ne=
gate ModuleDef</code>) and invents descriptions to fit. That's fine for fuz=
zing: the mutator still changes program structure and opens new paths, and =
the <a href=3D"https://nowarp.io/blog/compiler-testing-part-1#validating-mu=
tators">Validating phase</a> catches anything that doesn't actually modify =
code or produces invalid syntax. Here's how <code>negate ModuleDef</code> g=
ot interpreted:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>"Find two <code>module NAME { ... }</code> declarations in the same file=
 and swap their identifiers, breaking fully-qualified callers and exercisin=
g the resolver's duplicate-symbol / shadowing paths."</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Differences from the paper:</p>
<ul>
<li>Batched generation =E2=80=94 8 operations per target per prompt, saves =
tokens</li>
<li>Caching and skip logic for batches that failed in the first iteration</=
li>
<li>A configuration option to prioritize specific target structures (e.g. r=
ecently-added <code>enum</code>/<code>match</code> for Sui Move)</li>
</ul>
<h4 class=3D"anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id=3D"implementing-mutator=
s">Implementing mutators<a class=3D"hash-link" aria-label=3D"Direct link to=
 Implementing mutators" title=3D"Direct link to Implementing mutators" href=
=3D"https://nowarp.io/blog/compiler-testing-part-1#implementing-mutators">=
=E2=80=8B</a></h4>
<p>The implement phase turns each <code>(Name, Description)</code> pair int=
o a compiled Rust mutator registered in the driver. The <a href=3D"https://=
github.com/nowarp/move-fuzz/blob/f59321cb299c4877d64493d4c0a95d2f54f5f7bc/c=
ustom_mutators/metamove/prompts/implement_mutator.txt" target=3D"_blank" re=
l=3D"noopener noreferrer">prompt</a> contains the =CE=BCAST API reference a=
nd a reference implementation (<code>SwapBinOp</code>). The LLM returns Rus=
t code as text =E2=80=94 it has no filesystem access. The <a href=3D"https:=
//github.com/nowarp/move-fuzz/blob/f59321cb299c4877d64493d4c0a95d2f54f5f7bc=
/custom_mutators/metamove/scripts/generate.py" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noo=
pener noreferrer">generation script</a> writes each response to <code>src/m=
utators/{name}.rs</code>, runs <code>cargo check</code>, and on failure sen=
ds the code plus compiler error back for a refinement pass (up to 10 rounds=
). Mutators that still don't compile are dropped.</p>
<p>Mutator quality varies =E2=80=94 many are simple, some are hallucinated.=
 That's fine at scale: each target project has 700=E2=80=931000 combination=
 ideas to invent mutators, and the <a href=3D"https://nowarp.io/blog/compil=
er-testing-part-1#validating-mutators">Validating phase</a> filters the one=
s that don't actually modify code or generate garbage. About 7% of mutators=
 needed manual fixes after validation to become useful.</p>
